'''Missionary dating''' is the act of a person of one religious faith, commonly [[Christianity]], [[dating]] a person with differing beliefs for the purpose of changing that person's beliefs or religion.<ref>{{cite web |publisher = [[About.com]] | url=http://christianteens.about.com/od/dating/a/MissionaryDatin.htm|title=The Challenges of Missionary Dating for Christian Teens|accessdate=2010-06-12}}</ref><ref name="Bolz">{{cite book|author=Shawn Bolz|title=The Nonreligious Guide to Dating and Being Single|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=j1pBFpJNwCcC&pg=PA94|accessdate=14 February 2013|publisher=Shawn Bolz|isbn=978-0-982-23703-8 |pages=94}}</ref>
Interfaith dating and [[interfaith marriage]] may—or may not—be undertaken in the expectation of converting one's partner, though it is not uncommon for romantic partners to seek to persuade one another to change when there are areas of disunity.<ref>{{cite web|author=Bjarne Holmes, Ph.D.|title=Can You Really Change Your Relationship|publisher = [[Psychology Today]] | url=http://www.psychologytoday.com/blog/love-the-numbers/201106/can-you-really-change-your-relationship}}</ref>
