'''Norsk Novaselskap''' (the Norwegian Nova Society) was a [[Norway|Norwegian]] society organizing amateur [[astronomer]]s in Norway. It was founded by [[Sigurd Einbu]]. Systematic observations and search for new variable [[star]]s was organised by the society. One of the most active members was [[Nobel laureate]] in chemistry, [[Odd Hassel]], who for more than 50 years observed [[comet]]s and variable stars.<ref>http://www.astronomi2009.no/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=140:70komet&catid=36:astro-nytt&Itemid=34 (Norwegian)</ref>

